Definition: Given a list of integers, keep only the integers that are even. Return the resultant list even if it empty ("[]"). An even integer is exactly divisible by 2.

Positive Examples.explanation: 175 and 7 are removed from the list because they are not even numbers.
None of the values in the input list is even so an empty list is returned.

Negative Examples.explanation: The output contains some numbers that are not even.
The output only included one instance of 306, even though it appears two times in the input list.
